<doc id="881791" wikidata="Q784633" url="?curid=881791" title="Nernier">
<text>Nernier (; ) is a French village on the southern shore of Lake Geneva, in the department of Haute-Savoie.

Administratively classified a &quot;commune,&quot; Nernier shares a medieval village center and floral displays with the larger and better-known neighbouring village of Yvoire.

