:formula_12

The real and complex homographies described above are instances of the quaternion homography where formula_13 is zero or formula_14, respectively.
Evidently the transform takes formula_15 and takes formula_16.

Evaluating this homography at formula_17 maps the versor formula_18 into its axis:
